Naxals kill two CPI(M) workers
Two Communist Party of India-Marxist (CPI-M) workers were shot dead by suspected Maoists on Sunday at Balarampur in Maoist-hit Purulia district.
According to police, a group of armed Maoists asked Kalipada Chakraborty and Sukumar Chakraborty to come out of their houses in Tilai village and shot them from close range at about 11.30 pm.
Both of them were active CPI-M workers, police said, adding the ultras left the bodies beside a jungle near the village.